con` component.  \n  \n## Reference  \n <xref:System.Windows.Forms.NotifyIcon>  \n Provides reference information on the class and its members.  \n  \n## Related Sections  \n [Controls to Use on Windows Forms](../../../../docs/framework/winforms/controls/controls-to-use-on-windows-forms.md)  \n Provides a complete list of Windows Forms controls, with links to information on their use.","nodes":[{"pos":[12,65],"content":"NotifyIcon Component (Windows Forms) | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"NotifyIcon Component (Windows Forms) | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,53]}]},{"pos":[687,723],"content":"NotifyIcon Component (Windows Forms)","linkify":"NotifyIcon Component (Windows Forms)","nodes":[{"content":"NotifyIcon Component (Windows Forms)","pos":[0,36]}]},{"content":"The Windows Forms <ph id=\"ph1\">`NotifyIcon`</ph> component displays icons in the status notification area of the taskbar for processes that run in the background and would not otherwise have user interfaces.","pos":[724,913],"source":"The Windows Forms `NotifyIcon` component displays icons in the status notification area of the taskbar for processes that run in the background and would not otherwise have user interfaces."},{"content":"An example would be a virus protection program that can be accessed by clicking an icon in the status notification area of the taskbar.","pos":[914,1049]},{"pos":[1058,1073],"content":"In This Section","linkify":"In This Section","nodes":[{"content":"In This Section","pos":[0,15]}]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>NotifyIcon Component Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../../docs/framework/winforms/controls/notifyicon-component-overview-windows-forms.md)</ept>","pos":[1077,1201],"source":"[NotifyIcon Component Overview](../../../../docs/framework/winforms/controls/notifyicon-component-overview-windows-forms.md)"},{"content":"Introduces the general concepts of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`NotifyIcon`</ph> component, which allows users to see icons for 